<table border=0 cellspacing=1 cellpadding=1>
	<tr>
		<td valign=middle align=left width=22><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=1 width=20 border=0></td>
		<td valign=middle align=right class="header">Managing A POP3 Account</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2"><hr size="1"></td></tr>
	<tr>
    <td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text">EKP Messaging allows POP3 
      emails to be retrieved and managed here. More than 1 POP3 account can be 
      created.</td>
  </tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="text"><IMG src="/help/images/clear.gif" height=5 width=1 border=0></td></tr>
	<tr><td valign=top align=left colspan="2" class="subheader">Create A New POP3 Account</td></tr>
    <tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">1.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Options > Manage 
      POP3 Account</strong> link. All POP3 accounts will be listed here.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">2.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>New POP3 Account</strong> 
      button.</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">3.</td>
		<td valign=top align=left class="text">
			Fill up the following fields:<br>
			<li>Account Name - User's email address</li>
			
      <li>Indicator Colour - Choose any colour to indicate that it is an email 
        message in the inbox</li>
			
      <li>Deliver New Messages To - Choose which folder to store the downloaded 
        email</li>
			<li>POP3 Server Name - POP3 server name or IP adrress</li>
			<li>POP3 Server Port - Leave it at default port 110</li>
			
      <li>Username - User's email address</li>
			<li>Password - POP3 email password</li>
			<li>Confirm Password - Retype POP3 email password</li>
			<li>Leave a copy of email on server - Choose this option if necessary</li>
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td valign=top align=left width=22 class="text">4.</td>
		
    <td valign=top align=left class="text">Click on the <strong>Submit</strong> 
      button to save the POP3 account details.</td>
	</tr>
</table>
